PLC Projects

Programmable Logic Controller Implementations

Analog Sensor Calibration Using Timed State Logic and Dynamic SCP Scaling

Implemented a two-stage analog calibration sequence with timed states and scan-based averaging to correct zero and span drift in sensor readings. Structured calibration logic using explicit state transitions and one-shot interrupts, separating data collection from final math for stable, deterministic behavior. Dynamically updated SCP scaling limits from calibrated values to maintain accurate 0â€“40% measurements during normal system operation.

Ladder Logic RSLogix 500

Mode-Based PLC Control for Conveyor & Filling System

Defined a clean I/O map and implemented numbered process modes to represent each conveyor and filling stage as a simple state machine. Separated logic into cycle (state detection) and controls (output decisions) routines, improving sequencing clarity, interlocks, and mutual exclusivity. Controlled conveyor and hopper outputs using mode comparisons with level-switch interlocks to ensure safe, deterministic filling behavior.

Ladder Logic RSLogix 500

Runtime Hour-meter with Event-Driven Timekeeping

Implemented a single 1-second TON heartbeat gated by the system-running input, using DN + ONS to generate deterministic, scan-safe time events. Built cascaded rollover logic (seconds â†’ minutes â†’ hours â†’ thousands of hours) using bounded integer registers with overflow consumption, not time comparisons. Designed natural pause and atomic reset behavior by gating the time source and explicitly clearing all accumulators and the timer, eliminating the need for a separate pause routine.

Ladder Logic RSLogix 500

PLC-Based Digital Flowmeter Simulation

Simulated a digital rotameter in PLC logic using a timed pulse input to represent flowmeter k-factor behavior. Converted pulse counts into real-time flow rate (GPM) using timers, counters, and math operations stored in a float register. Validated logic by adjusting pulse timing and observing stable flow calculations across different operating rates.

Ladder Logic RSLogix 500

RLC Projects

Relay Logic & Control Implementations

Forward/Reverse Starter + Indication Lamps

Built a classic forward and reverse motor control where only one direction energized at a time using electrical interlocking with NC auxiliary contacts and seal in holding logic. Added status lamps driven by auxiliary contacts so the panel clearly indicated the active operating state at all times.

Star-Delta Starter

Built the full star delta motor starter where the power wiring demonstrated how the motor windings were switched between star and delta, and the control wiring enforced mutual exclusivity so star and delta could not energize together through timer sequencing and interlocking. This project combined power path reasoning with control logic timing and sequencing.

Sensor Wiring + Relay Card + Complex Interlocking

Modeled a real automation pattern where sensors provided 24VDC logic, a relay card converted the low voltage logic into switched AC outputs, and interlocking ensured that only one actuator path was allowed at a time similar to forward reverse interlocking but driven by sensor inputs. This project reinforced correct PNP and NPN behavior and the principle that only one logical path could be true at a time.

Robotics-CAD Work

Advanced simulation and computer-aided design projects

UR20 Cobot Welding Simulation â€“ RV Ladder Workcell Integration

I designed the RV ladder and fixturing in Autodesk Inventor and Fusion 360, then imported the CAD models into RoboDK to build and validate a UR20 cobot welding simulation, ensuring proper robot envelope coverage, collision clearance, and realistic approach paths based on the actual table layout. Using the RoboDK Python API, I automated weld path generation and simulated the weld trail along the programmed trajectory to verify full weld coverage and motion consistency before physical implementation.
